translated: Brunnström, Axel Wilhelm Leopold, Lieutenant Colonel, from Halmstad. Born on June 11th, 1863 in Ramlösa, Malmöhus County, the son of Major Rudolph B. and Christine Engeström. He married Augusta Ehrenborg in 1893 and they had four children: Ellen (born 1894), Edith (born 1895), Carin (born 1896), and Leopold (born 1897). Brunnström attended the Cavalry School from 1884-1885 and the equestrian school in Saumur from 1887-1888. He attended a tactical training course for captains and majors in 1907. He served as a second lieutenant in the North Scanian Infantry Regiment in 1882 and in the Scanian Dragoon Regiment in 1884. He became a lieutenant in 1893, a captain in 1903, and a major in the Norrland Dragoon Regiment in 1908 and in the Scanian Dragoon Regiment in 1910. He became a Lieutenant Colonel in the Crown Prince's Hussar Regiment in 1913. He served in the Dutch Cavalry in 1908. Brunnström was a member of the Military Committee at the International Equestrian Competition in Turin in 1911, and the inspector of distilleries and malt liquor manufacturers from 1921-1923. He was awarded the Order of the Sword, the Order of Vasa, and the Royal Order of the Netherlands Lion, among other honors.
